==English==
===Noun===
'''Aspie'''
#[[Aspergerian]]; a [[nickname]] given to people who have [[Asperger's Syndrome]]. It is considered more friendly and affectionate than "person with Asperger's Syndrome", "person with a mild form of autism", and "Asperger's sufferer".
#Name given to people who have another [[autistic spectrum disorder]] such as [[high-functioning autism]].

===Usage note===
*The female form of "aspie" is "[[aspiette]]", although "aspie" can be used to describe both genders.